<mujoco model="k1_robocup_scene">
  <!--
    RoboCup Humanoid League KidSize field scene for the vendored Booster K1
    (see K1_22dof.xml / VENDORED.md). Field/goal dimensions ported from this
    repo's Webots assets: worlds/k1_robocup.wbt (layout, spawn poses, contact
    coefficients) and protos/robocup_field/RobocupSoccerField.proto +
    RobocupGoal.proto (KidSize dimensions: field 9x6 m playing area + 1 m
    border, goal 2.6 m wide x 1.2 m high, center circle radius 0.75 m, goal
    area 1x3 m, penalty area 2x5 m, penalty mark 1.5 m from the goal line).

    The field texture and ball texture in protos/robocup_field/ are licensed
    "Copyright Cyberbotics Ltd., for use only with Webots" (see e.g.
    RobocupTexturedSoccerBall.proto header) or reference an external
    cyberbotics/webots Grass.proto -- neither is redistributable here, so
    the pitch is rendered procedurally instead: a green checker material
    plus painted white line markings built from thin box geoms at the
    standard KidSize line positions (approximate, per task brief).

    Solver settings (timestep 0.001, Newton, impratio 10) come from the
    included K1_22dof.xml and are intentionally not overridden here.

    Ball body layout note: the "ball" body is declared at pos="0 0 0" with
    its sphere geom offset to pos="1.38 0 0.0785" (rather than putting that
    offset on the body itself). This is deliberate: K1_22dof.xml's own
    "ready"/"lying_front"/"lying_back" keyframes were authored with qpos
    sized for the bare robot (nq=29); once this scene adds the ball's
    freejoint (nq becomes 36), MuJoCo silently zero-pads the missing 7
    ball qpos entries in those inherited keyframes to (0,0,0,1,0,0,0)
    (verified: it pads with zero, not with the body's qpos0/pos attribute,
    and MuJoCo rejects two <key> elements sharing a name, so the keyframes
    cannot simply be redefined here). Zeroing the *body* frame and offsetting
    the *geom* means that zero-padded default is exactly the intended rest
    pose, so the ball lands at (1.38, 0, 0.0785) under all three inherited
    keyframes with no scene-level keyframe override required.

    A dedicated "kickoff" keyframe below places the robot at the match-start
    spawn pose (mirrors the Webots world's red K1 at translation -2.71 0 0.53,
    rotation 0 i.e. facing +x) using the same joint angles as "ready" (its
    own base height retuned to 0.555, like "ready" -- see VENDORED.md).
  -->
